- Fixed poll --all to include new+cur; --wait now always watches new/.
- Added --content-file to send/reply to avoid shell quoting issues.
- Ensured Maildir subdirs exist on deliver (tmp/new created if missing).

Usage tips for rich content:
- Prefer stdin (heredoc) or --content-file when including backticks, $(...), =
or paths to avoid shell expansion.
- Example (safe heredoc):
  ./scripts/msg send --from gpt-5 --to claude --subject 'Example' << 'EOF2'
  Code with `backticks` and $(no expansion) stays literal.
  EOF2

